{
  "book": 13,
  "chapter": 1,
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "從亞當到亞伯拉罕"
    },
    {
      "type": "ref-heading",
      "heading": "（創5‧1－32；10‧1－32；11‧10－26）"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 1,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Adam, Seth, Enosh; "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 2,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Kenan, Mahalalel, Jared; "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 3,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Enoch, Methuselah, Lamech; "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 5,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Japheth: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech, and Tiras. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Riphath, and Togarmah. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Javan: Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Rodanim. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Ham: Cush, Egypt, Put, and Canaan. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Cush: Seba, Havilah, Sabta, Raamah, and Sabteca. The sons of Raamah: Sheba and Dedan. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Cush fathered Nimrod. He was the first on earth to be a mighty man. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Egypt fathered Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Naphtuhim, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Pathrusim, Casluhim (from whom the Philistines came), and Caphtorim. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Canaan fathered Sidon his firstborn and Heth, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "and the Jebusites, the Amorites, the Girgashites, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "the Hivites, the Arkites, the Sinites, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "the Arvadites, the Zemarites, and the Hamathites. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Shem: Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, and Aram. And the sons of Aram: Uz, Hul, Gether, and Meshech. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 18,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Arpachshad fathered Shelah, and Shelah fathered Eber. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 19,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "To Eber were born two sons: the name of the one was Peleg (for in his days the earth was divided), and his brother’s name was Joktan. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 20,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Joktan fathered Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 21,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 22,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Obal, Abimael, Sheba, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 23,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab; all these were the sons of Joktan. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 23,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 24,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Shem, Arpachshad, Shelah; "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 25,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Eber, Peleg, Reu; "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 26,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Serug, Nahor, Terah; "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 27,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Abram, that is, Abraham. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "以實瑪利的後裔"
    },
    {
      "type": "ref-heading",
      "heading": "（創25‧12－16）"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 27,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 28,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Abraham: Isaac and Ishmael. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 29,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "These are their genealogies: the firstborn of Ishmael, Nebaioth, and Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 30,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 31,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. These are the sons of Ishmael. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 32,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Keturah, Abraham’s concubine: she bore Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah. The sons of Jokshan: Sheba and Dedan. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 33,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Midian: Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah. All these were the descendants of Keturah. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "以掃的後裔"
    },
    {
      "type": "ref-heading",
      "heading": "（創36‧1－19）"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 33,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 34,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Abraham fathered Isaac. The sons of Isaac: Esau and Israel. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 35,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Esau: Eliphaz, Reuel, Jeush, Jalam, and Korah. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 36,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Eliphaz: Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam, Kenaz, and of Timna, Amalek. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 37,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "以東地的原住民"
    },
    {
      "type": "ref-heading",
      "heading": "（創36‧20－30）"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 37,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 38,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Seir: Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 39,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Lotan: Hori and Hemam; and Lotan’s sister was Timna. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 40,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Shobal: Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho, and Onam. The sons of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 41,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The son of Anah: Dishon. The sons of Dishon: Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 42,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan. The sons of Dishan: Uz and Aran. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "heading": "以東諸王"
    },
    {
      "type": "ref-heading",
      "heading": "（創36‧31－43）"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 42,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 43,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "These are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before any king reigned over the people of Israel: Bela the son of Beor, the name of his city being Dinhabah. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 44,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Bela died, and Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his place. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 45,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Jobab died, and Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his place. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 46,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Husham died, and Hadad the son of Bedad, who defeated Midian in the country of Moab, reigned in his place, the name of his city being Avith. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 47,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Hadad died, and Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his place. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 48,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Samlah died, and Shaul of Rehoboth on the Euphrates reigned in his place. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 49,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Shaul died, and Baal-hanan, the son of Achbor, reigned in his place. "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 50,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Baal-hanan died, and Hadad reigned in his place, the name of his city being Pai; and his wife’s name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 50,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 51,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "And Hadad died. The chiefs of Edom were: chiefs Timna, Alvah, Jetheth, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 52,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Oholibamah, Elah, Pinon, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 53,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Kenaz, Teman, Mibzar, "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 54,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Magdiel, and Iram; these are the chiefs of Edom. "
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}